Eurozone crisis as it happened: Day two of Iberia strikes after clashes with police
European markets have been lifted by a positive German business confidence survey and a positive start on Wall Street after Monday's Presidents day holiday in the US.
• The FTSE 100 has ended 0.96% higher at 6379.07, a new five year high
• The Athens market is 1.12% better
• In the US, the Dow Jones Industrial Average is currently up 41 points
But sterling has fallen to new 7-months lows ahead of UK unemployment figures and Bank of England minutes tomorrow, amid yet another spate of talk about a possible downgrading of the UK's AAA credit rating.
And with that, we'll close up for the evening. Thanks for all the comments and we'll be back tomorrow.